name: Jessica Bell
description: I am a born and raised Winnipegger, having lived independently in most major areas of the city, my preference is to stay close to the hustle and bustle of downtown Winnipeg. Professionally I started out freelancing Social Media Services, Marketing, Content Writing, Design, and am in the midst of my freelance hobbies being turned into a full fledge start-up. Personally, I love to explore, learn and create. I enjoy studying and practice with energy & holistic healing methods such as Aromatherapy, Reiki and Hypnotherapy. I spend much of my free time walking our city sites, river walks and downtown sidewalks with my trusty pup, soaking in the unique history, architecture and culture Winnipeg has to offer.

name: Susan Ainley
description:
Susan Ainley, in a reversal of the usual trend, relocated to downtown Winnipeg nine years ago from Alberta.  

Walking and biking everywhere, she loves the convenience of living in the heart of the city, where she can start the day walking her dog through the Forks, go for brunch with pals, shop unique boutiques in the Exchange in the afternoon and finish the day enjoying any of the many festivals and cultural events that happen year-round. 

Her instagram follows her day-to-day celebration of everything great in downtown Winnipeg.

@graph.name: Susan Ainley
@graph.description: Susan Ainley, in a reversal of the usual trend, relocated to downtown Winnipeg nine years ago from Alberta. Walking and biking everywhere, she loves the convenience of living in the heart of the city, where she can start the day walking her dog through the Forks, go for brunch with pals, shop unique boutiques in the Exchange in the afternoon and finish the day enjoying any of the many festivals and cultural events that happen year-round. Her instagram follows her day-to-day celebration of everything great in downtown Winnipeg.
